    "project_id": 278964,
    "id": 469660681,
    "iid": 229842,
    "title": "ci: Skip pipeline on auto-deploy branch creation",
    "description": "## What does this MR do and why?\n\nDo not create a pipeline when an auto-deploy branch (matching `^\\d+-\\d+-auto-deploy-\\d+$`) is first created (branch creation push), but still allow pipelines to run for subsequent commits pushed to the branch.\n\nWe use `CI_COMMIT_BEFORE_SHA` to detect branch creation. According to the [predefined variables documentation](https://docs.gitlab.com/ci/variables/predefined_variables/), it is:\n\n> \"always 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 for merge request pipelines, scheduled pipelines, the first commit in pipelines for branches or tags, or when manually running a pipeline\"\n\n## How to set up and validate locally\n\nThe workflow rule change was validated on https://gitlab.com/dat.tang.gitlab/test-gitlab-ci using an equivalent `workflow.rules` config.\n\n1. Create a new auto-deploy branch from `main` - no pipeline should be triggered:\n   * There is only one pipeline on the `main` pipeline for the commit https://gitlab.com/dat.tang.gitlab/test-gitlab-ci/-/commit/7745d874e3896607425c274e4e0c8a7d6765cca6/pipelines\n2. Push a commit to that branch - a pipeline should run:\n   * There is a new pipeline run on the new commit on the `auto-deploy` branch https://gitlab.com/dat.tang.gitlab/test-gitlab-ci/-/commit/9909d2dd6fdd599e44421ab06ee4209cbe0cacdb/pipelines\n\n## MR acceptance checklist\n\n- [x] This MR does not require a documentation update.\n\nRef: https://gitlab.com/gitlab-com/gl-infra/delivery/-/work_items/21965",
